Turning Cash Digital Options

system

user

2025-07-01T14:40:45.543612Z user

So I owe cash app money so thats out of the question right now but how else can I turn cash digital - Im at Walmart rn - I have Venmo but I dont have the physical card where I can locate it rn - just a prepaid debit card or something?

2025-07-01T14:40:47.599817Z assistant

Got it you're trying to digitize cash while at Walmart, but Cash App is out, and Venmo is active but your card is MIA. Here are a few solid workarounds thatll get your physical cash turned digital ASAP:

Top Option (Right Now at Walmart): Buy a Prepaid Debit Card

Walmart sells prepaid Visa, Mastercard, and American Express cards. Heres how to use them smartly:

  • Buy a Reloadable Prepaid Card (e.g., Netspend, Green Dot, or Walmart MoneyCard).
  • Load cash at the register (you tell them how much you want to load).
  • Register it online (some require this before online use).
  • Use it just like a debit card online or to fund Venmo/PayPal, etc.

Avoid the gift versions if possible go for reloadable ones with online account access.

Can You Fund Venmo With a Prepaid Card?

Yes, Venmo allows many prepaid cards (Visa/MasterCard) as long as theyre registered to your name and have online access. Once added:

  1. Open Venmo > go to Settings > Payment Methods.
  2. Tap Add Bank or Card > Choose Card.
  3. Enter the prepaid card info.

Other In-Store Options (If You Want to Fund a Wallet or Account Digitally)

1. Walmart2Walmart or Ria Money Transfer

  • Send money to yourself (or a trusted contact) who can accept it digitally.
  • Fees are low if staying in-network.

2. Buy a PayPal My Cash Card

  • Add money to your PayPal account via Walmart using this card.
  • Then use PayPal to transfer to bank, pay people, etc.

Quick Recap

Option What You Need Can Use With Venmo? Fee?
Prepaid reloadable card Cash + ID + phone Yes ~$35
Walmart PayPal My Cash Card PayPal account Not directly ~$3.95
Walmart2Walmart transfer Valid ID + sender info Low
Ria Money Transfer Cash + ID Low

If you tell me how much cash youre trying to digitize and your goal (e.g., pay someone, buy online, load Venmo, etc.), I can narrow it down even more.

You're sitting on cash, and youve got no active Cash App and no Venmo card handy, but you do have a Walmart nearby. Heres a laser-focused path forward using PayPal + a prepaid card to digitize your cash and knock both tasks out:

Primary Strategy: Walmart Prepaid Card PayPal Pay Bills & Airbnb

Step 1: Buy a Reloadable Prepaid Debit Card at Walmart

Go for one of these, in this order:

  • Walmart MoneyCard (reloadable, made for this kind of thing)
  • Green Dot Visa or Mastercard (widely accepted)
  • Netspend (also works with PayPal/Venmo)

Important: Avoid gift-only cards ask for reloadable. These support identity verification and online transactions.

Step 2: Register and Add to PayPal
